The article is a Presidential Proclamation by Barack Obama declaring October 4, 2010, as Child Health Day. The proclamation emphasizes the importance of providing children with quality healthcare, nutritious food, clean air and water, and safe environments. It also addresses the issue of childhood obesity and the need to address it as a national health crisis. The Affordable Care Act is mentioned as a means to ensure children have access to healthcare regardless of pre-existing conditions. The proclamation also highlights the need to protect children from environmental exposures and encourages collaboration between various stakeholders to ensure the health and well-being of children.